LAFIA –  As the primary elections of the All Progressives Congress (APC) draws near, over 10,000 youths and women in Nasarawa State have marched in support of Governor Yahaya Bello”s presidential ambition in 2023. The marchers, comprising various groups supporting the Kogi governor, said the rally was to express their confidence in Bello’s leadership qualities, and to appeal to APC delegates to vote for him in the forthcoming presidential primary election. Nasarawa State Chairman of Yahaya Bello Network, Ibrahim Lawal Ibrahim, who led the marchers in Lafia, said they were on a mission to see that Yahaya Bello becomes the president in 2023. -Advertisement- “Yahaya Bello has done a lot in terms of security, there is no single case of insecurity in Kogi, as such making him the president would do good things in terms of security in Nigeria.” Also speaking, the Coordinator, Recuse Nigeria Mission, Tahir Nagogo, said that the youths in Nasarawa State would vote for Yahaya Bello for president come 2023. “We are here to make a difference and to make a change, we are not voting for anybody except Yahaya Bello because he is trusted to make a change in 2023,” he stated.